<runspec version="MOVES5.0.1">
	<description><![CDATA[Auxiliary Power Exhaust (process 91) at County (SINGLE) scale — vacuous reference (issue #39).

Canonical MOVES 5.0.1 emits NO inventory for process 91 (APU / hotelling). Its
BaseRateCalculator.sql reads the hotellingHours activity in GetActivity (Section
Process91), but the worker-output step never lands process-91 rows in
MOVESOutput/BaseRateOutput: every captured snapshot is empty for process 90/91,
including the fully-populated default-scale process-apu fixture (358 baseRate_91_2020
rate rows, non-zero APU op-mode-201 fraction, non-zero hotellingHours, diesel fuel
supply — and still 0 output rows). See docs/known-divergences.md §4.5.

The scale gate (scale_canonical_snapshot_diff) therefore asserts a VACUOUS match:
canonical 0 rows == port 0 rows. The port correctly emits nothing; a future
over-emission fails the gate.

Provides a scale-input directory with hotellingHours.parquet (county hotelling activity)
and hotellingActivityDistribution.parquet. Snapshot captured with canonical MOVES 5.0.1
against the Washtenaw County CDB.]]></description>
